  "prompt": "Why isn't Snoop Dogg arrested for smoking marijuana?",
  "response": "Snoop Dogg is a well-known advocate for marijuana use and has been open about his consumption of cannabis for many years. His public persona is closely tied to marijuana culture. \n\nIn many places, marijuana has been legalized for recreational use, and Snoop Dogg often operates in contexts where such laws permit his behavior. In states where marijuana is legalized, he can legally smoke without fear of arrest. Additionally, his high-profile status and association with the entertainment industry mean that he often has access to environments where cannabis use is accepted.\n\nIt's also worth noting that public figures can sometimes navigate legal issues differently than the general public, often possessing resources that allow them to manage legal repercussions more effectively.",
